{
  "string_app_name": "write-a-fun",
  "string_original_requirement": "Write a fun quiz with question and answers. Make the questions strange to ffol people into wring answers, like a word game setup to fail",
  "string_formal_spec": "FUNCTIONS: \nget_string_question() \nget_string_answer() \nget_bool_is_correct() \nset_bool_is_correct() \nget_list_questions() \nget_dict_question_to_answer() \nsave_string_question_to_state() \nsave_string_answer_to_state() \nget_string_current_question() \nget_string_current_answer() \nrun_bool_quiz_on_string_question() \nset_int_score() \nget_int_score() \nget_string_result_message() \nget_bool_is_game_over() \nset_bool_is_game_over() \nget_list_possible_answers() \nget_string_random_question() \nget_string_random_answer() \nsave_list_questions_to_state() \nsave_dict_question_to_answer_to_state() \n\nINPUTS: \nget_string_question(): none \nget_string_answer(): string_question \nget_bool_is_correct(): string_answer, string_correct_answer \nset_bool_is_correct(): bool_is_correct \nget_list_questions(): none \nget_dict_question_to_answer(): none \nsave_string_question_to_state(): string_question \nsave_string_answer_to_state(): string_answer \nget_string_current_question(): none \nget_string_current_answer(): none \nrun_bool_quiz_on_string_question(): string_question \nset_int_score(): int_score \nget_int_score(): none \nget_string_result_message(): bool_is_correct \nget_bool_is_game_over(): none \nset_bool_is_game_over(): bool_is_game_over \nget_list_possible_answers(): string_question \nget_string_random_question(): none \nget_string_random_answer(): none \nsave_list_questions_to_state(): list_questions \nsave_dict_question_to_answer_to_state(): dict_question_to_answer \n\nOUTPUTS: \nget_string_question(): string \nget_string_answer(): string \nget_bool_is_correct(): bool \nset_bool_is_correct(): none \nget_list_questions(): list_string \nget_dict_question_to_answer(): dict_string_to_string \nsave_string_question_to_state(): none \nsave_string_answer_to_state(): none \nget_string_current_question(): string \nget_string_current_answer(): string \nrun_bool_quiz_on_string_question(): bool \nset_int_score(): none \nget_int_score(): int \nget_string_result_message(): string \nget_bool_is_game_over(): bool \nset_bool_is_game_over(): none \nget_list_possible_answers(): list_string \nget_string_random_question(): string \nget_string_random_answer(): string \nsave_list_questions_to_state(): none \nsave_dict_question_to_answer_to_state(): none \n\nCONSTRAINTS: \nall functions must be in snake_case \nall functions must have a single job \nno nesting of functions \nno classes \nno this keyword \nall mutable state must be in state.ts \nevery mutable global must have a set_<name>() setter \nall types must be flat and max 2 levels deep \nRecord<string,string> must be used for dicts \nno Map, Set, or Symbol \nasync/await must be used for asynchronous code \nno .then() callbacks \nalways try/catch \nnever empty catch \nalways log before throw \nnever throw inside a Promise .then() callback \ndead code must be removed before export \nevery exported function must be used or be a test hook \nno fs.existsSync on fs/promises \nuse fs.mkdir({ recursive: true }) instead \nno execution of code at top level \nguard self-tests: if (require.main === module) { ... } \nno unused imports \none import per line \nno wildcards \nJS output format must be raw JS only \nno markdown fences \nno TypeScript \nconst/let never var \nfunction declarations \nmodule.exports = { fn1, fn2, ... } at bottom",
  "int_last_passing_revision": 4
}